Installation Manual: FTL 0.1.0
------------------------------

Prequisites:

  source archive: libftl-0.1.0.tar.gz
  configurator:   cmake (>2.8.0)
  builder:        gnumake (depends on cmake)
  compiler:       g++ (>3.3.6)

Extract source archive:

  mkdir -p ~/tmp
  cd ~/tmp
  tar xzvf libftl-0.1.0.tar.gz
  mv libftl-0.1.0 libftl-src

Build shared versions of the library:

  mkdir -p ~/tmp/libftl/debug ~/tmp/libftl/release
  cd ~/tmp/libftl/debug
  cmake -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release ~/tmp/libftl-src
  make
  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release
  cmake -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug ~/tmp/libftl-src
  make

Build static version of the library (optional):

  cd ~/tmp/libftl/debug-static
  cmake -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -D BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=OFF ~/tmp/libftl-src
  make
  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release-static
  cmake -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -D BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=OFF ~/tmp/libftl-src
  make

Configure special options on Mac OS X (optional):

  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release
  cmake -D CMAKE_OSX_SYSROOT=/Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.5.sdk \
        -D CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=10.5 \
        -D CMAKE_OSX_ARCHITECTURES=x86_64\;i386\;ppc $PWD
  make

Switch to verbose build mode (optional):

  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release
  cmake -D CMAKE_VERBOSE_MAKEFILE=ON $PWD
  make clean && make

Change installation prefix (optional):

  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release
  cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr $PWD
  make

Install in default locations (optional):

  cd ~/tmp/libftl/release
  sudo make install
